# Object pool (ScenePool)

**Design SSOT:** [`Docs/Architecture/Architecture_Pool.md`](../../Docs/Architecture/Architecture_Pool.md)

## Must (pooled node script)

- Implement `pool_reset()` and `pool_on_acquire()` for nodes that re-enter play.
- Do not use `_ready()` for per-spawn setup (runs once). Spawn state belongs in `pool_on_acquire` or caller setup (e.g. `Mob.initialize_spawn_health`).
- Remove gameplay groups in `pool_reset` (`mobs`, `exp_orbs`); re-add in `pool_on_acquire`.
- End lifetime with `PoolUtil.release_node(self)`, not `queue_free()`, when the node was acquired from the pool.

## Must (spawn callers)

- Mobs: `Game.spawn_mob()` â†’ `%MapArena.get_random_spawn_position(%Player.global_position)` â†’ `ScenePool.acquire(..., spawn_pos)` â†’ `initialize_spawn_health`.
- Exp orbs / gold: `mob.gd` `_die()` â†’ `acquire(EXP_ORB_SCENE` / `GOLD_COIN_SCENE`, parent) â†’ set position/value.
- Player projectiles / area / orbit: `AttackFactory._acquire` (via `Gun.shoot()` or `loadout_grant_passive`) â†’ setup â†’ `PoolUtil.release_node` on end.
- Mob ranged: telegraph â†’ `acquire(MOB_ATTACK_MARK_SCENE)` â†’ timer â†’ release mark â†’ `acquire(MOB_PROJECTILE_SCENE)` â†’ `PoolUtil.release_node` on projectile end.
- Mob charge lane: `acquire(MOB_CHARGE_LANE_SCENE)` â†’ `setup_world` â†’ lane self-release.

## Must (mob pool)

- `pool_reset`: clear status/telegraphs, `collision_layer = 0`, `collision_mask = 0`.
- `pool_on_acquire`: `PhysicsLayers.apply_mob_body()`, `add_to_group("mobs")`.
- `_die()` must still call `Game.register_kill()` before `PoolUtil.release_node(self)`.

## When adding a new mob scene

- Update `MobSpawnSelector`, `scene_pool.gd` `MOB_PREWARM_SCENE_PATHS`, and active `BalanceTable` in the same change.

## When adding a new pooled scene

- Add `pool_reset` / `pool_on_acquire`, use `PoolUtil.release_node` on end, wire acquire via `AttackFactory`, `Game.spawn_mob`, or direct `ScenePool.acquire`.
- Add prewarm `@export` + `_ready()` entry on `ScenePool` if the type spawns frequently.

## Must not

- Do not rename or remove `ObjectPools` without updating `game.gd`, `attack_factory.gd`, `gun.gd`, `mob.gd`, and grep for `ObjectPools` / `ScenePool`.
- Do not `queue_free()` pooled mobs, exp orbs, gold coins, or gun/attack-managed projectiles while pooling is enabled (breaks pool invariants).
